The paper describes a type of neural network, which suggests it belongs to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The paper also focuses on optimization methods and their comparison, which is relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The problem of factorization is a common task in artificial intelligence, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of nonlinear dynamics and interconnected Hopfield Networks suggests the paper may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with high-dimensional vectors, which is relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
